The article highlights the united condemnation of Russia's aggression against Ukraine and expresses solidarity with the Ukrainian people. The United States and the European Union have strengthened and aligned their sanctions regimes, imposing severe costs on Russia for its actions. Efforts are being made to monitor the implementation of sanctions and prevent evasion. Humanitarian assistance is being provided to support the Ukrainian people affected by the conflict. The European Union has welcomed millions of Ukrainian refugees and the United States plans to welcome up to 100,000 Ukrainian refugees. Commitments are being made to promote democratic resilience, human rights, and accountability in Ukraine and neighboring countries. Energy security, global food supplies, cybersecurity, and combatting the illicit use of digital assets are also addressed in the article.